 Mount Road police detectives have appealed to the public for assistance with information that can assist them in tracing the family of a person, who was involved in an accident during the early hours of Friday morning. According to police information, at about 01:00, a white Suzuki 600CC motorbike with a Cape Town registration allegedly collided into a lamp post on the Cotswold bridge in Port Elizabeth. "The unknown rider was taken to Livingstone hospital," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "He is a white male, age unknown and was wearing a pair of black pants and black shirt." Anyone who may know this person or family of this person is asked to contact D/Lt Col Melanie Orange at SAPS Mount Road on 0824418505 or 041 3946316. 